1 unit(s) Black Beans
½ cup Quick Oats
2 unit(s) Artisan Bun
28 g Crispy Shallots
4 tbsp Chipotle Sauce
28 g Spring Mix
2 unit(s) Sweet Potato
1 tsp Garlic Salt
2 tbsp Mayonnaise
90 mL Dill Pickle, sliced
100 g Bacon Strips
2 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Cut sweet potatoes into 1/2-inch wedges.
Add sweet potatoes and 1 tbsp oil to a parchment-lined baking sheet. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, use 2 parchment-lined baking sheets, with 1 tbsp oil per sheet.) Season with 1/2 tsp garlic salt and pepper, then toss coat. Roast in the middle of the oven, flipping halfway through, until tender and golden-brown, 22-24 min. (NOTE: For 4 ppl, roast in the middle and bottom of the oven, rotating sheets halfway through.)

Arrange bacon strips in a single layer on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Roast bacon in the top of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 8-12 min.**
Meanwhile, drain and rinse black beans.
Add beans and oats to a large bowl. Mash to a chunky consistency.
Add half the chipotle sauce, 1/2 tsp (1 tsp) garlic salt and half the crispy shallots.
Stir to combine.
Form mixture into three (six) TK-inch-wide patties.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium heat. When hot, add 1 tbsp oil, then patties. (NOTE: Don't overcrowd the pan; cook patties in 2 batches if needed.) Pan-fry until golden-brown, 4-6 min per side. Transfer to a plate.

Meanwhile, strain pickles.
Halve buns.
Arrange on an unlined baking sheet, cut-side up. Toast buns in the top of the oven until golden-brown, 3-4 min. (TIP: Keep an eye on buns so they don't burn.)

Spread mayo over buns.
Stack remaining shallots, patties (use 2 patties for 2 ppl and 4 for 4 ppl), bacon, spring mix and pickles on bottom buns. Close with top buns. (NOTE: Enjoy extra patties for breakfast or lunch with eggs!)

Divide burgers and sweet potatoes between plates.
Serve remaining chipotle sauce on the side for dipping.

If you've opted to add bacon, arrange bacon strips in a single layer on a parchment-lined baking sheet. Roast bacon in the top of the oven until crispy and cooked through, 8-12 min.**

Top burgers with bacon when you assemble them.